<p>This is my prolog file.</p>  <pre><code>male(bob). male(john).  female(betty). female(dana).  father(bob, john). father(bob, dana). mother(betty, john). mother(betty, dana).  husband(X, Y) :- male(X), mother(Y, Z), father(X, Z). wife(X, Y) :- female(X), father(Y, Z), mother(X, Z). son(X, Y) :- male(X), mother(Y, X);female(X), father(Y, X). daughter(X, Y) :- female(X), mother(Y, X);female(X), father(Y, X). sister(X, Y) :- female(X), mother(Z, X), mother(Z, Y), X \= Y. brother(X, Y) :- male(X), mother(Z, X), mother(Z, Y), X \= Y. </code></pre>  <p>I want a name of rule if it returns true for any value x or y. Let's say <code>x = betty</code> and <code>y = john</code>.</p>  <p><code>mother(betty, john).</code> &lt;- this will meet so my rule should return 'mother'. Similarly if any other rule or fact meets true for some value x, y it should return that rule name.</p>  <p>How can I achieve something like that?</p>